cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SD, cs.MS, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper is about early prediction of software quality and the influence of software complexity metrics on quality attributes. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions Chidamber and Kemerer metric suite, which is a set of object-oriented programming metrics. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is another possible category as the paper discusses the relationship between design complexity and testing effort. 
- cs.MS (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a tailored meta-analysis approach to aggregate data. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is unlikely as there is no mention of cryptography or security in the paper.
